snippet.textDisplay: I know you guys get so many requests about different scenes from movies and shows. But I was wondering as my Wife and I sat down to watch both Narnias and immediately noticed the Aslan from Narnia 1 is a whole lot better than the Aslan from Narnia 2. I was trying to recognize the difference between the two and even the different CG characters through out these movies, some looking better than others. Also I enjoy the sacrifice scene in the first Narnia because it looked like to me that all those creatures were using prosthetics and were life like puppets and not CG.
snippet.textOriginal: I know you guys get so many requests about different scenes from movies and shows. But I was wondering as my Wife and I sat down to watch both Narnias and immediately noticed the Aslan from Narnia 1 is a whole lot better than the Aslan from Narnia 2. I was trying to recognize the difference between the two and even the different CG characters through out these movies, some looking better than others. Also I enjoy the sacrifice scene in the first Narnia because it looked like to me that all those creatures were using prosthetics and were life like puppets and not CG.

snippet.textDisplay: Pretty much everyone in my generation that is into the VR stuff today, wanted VR since The Lawnmower Man and they used to hold this movie as the best VR movie until The Matrix came out. My feelings of VR align with my feelings of this movie. A friend recently asked me will I finally get a VR set for new Half Life game. I literately said that I've visited and left the VR hype train in 1992.
